ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The etiology (or etiologies) of this cluster of cases is not yet reported.
It would not be surprising if there are several pathogens involved here,
some bacterial, some protozoal and some viral. A large-number outbreak in a
localized area, even if occurring in the developed world, can easily
outrace any surge capacity of a health care system. - Mod.LL]. [Given the
sudden onset of huge number of cases, some hyperacute, in a limited area,
I would rather suspect acute toxicity than any infectious etiology.
Probably some industry dumped a poisonous product into the sewers which
leaked into the local water supply. - Mod.JW]
